                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/1554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hood</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-07T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 7, 1922—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Your number 33, September 27, 3 P.M.</p>
                <p>I am authorized by the President to say that final favorable action on Liberian
                    Loan Bill will be urged again at the next session of the Congress, but that
                    inasmuch as Congress will not reconvene until early in December, final action
                    cannot be expected before the latter part of that month. You may so inform
                    Liberian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
